Store
===============================================================================

The store is the runtime component responsible for runtime records.

It is separate from the language data model. Language values are program data; store records are runtime metadata and state.

1. Store responsibilities
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A runtime store may record:

- Runtime records.
- Module records and module versions.
- Import edges.
- Task records.
- Actor records.
- Message records.
- Object records.
- Transaction records.

2. Default store
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The default runtime uses an in-memory store.

External hosts can provide another store implementation through the runtime builder.

3. Durable storage
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Durable storage is a store implementation concern. It should not be configured through scalar runtime config alone.
